cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.GR 

This paper proposes a novel approach for image segmentation that combines Neural Ordinary Differential Equations (NODEs) and the Level Set method. The paper focuses on computer vision tasks such as kidney segmentation and salient object detection, which are typically categorized under computer vision (cs.CV). The use of NODEs and deep learning models also suggests that the paper could be categorized under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also proposes a method for evolving an image embedding into a dense per-pixel semantic label space, which could be categorized under neural networks (cs.NE) or graphics (cs.GR).
